A simple Hall Reservation App using Django and DRF.

All requirement details are in requirements.txt

Concept used:
 -MVT architecture
 -Class based Views and Functional Based Views
 -Django signals
 -Django Sessions
 -Forms
 -Django templates
 -Serializers


List all Halls present: http://127.0.0.1:8000/hall/
Form for Booking a hall and will show the available halls: http://127.0.0.1:8000/hall/book
Then,User will get get a list of halls that are available for the booking at a specific time.
User will click on Book and id of hall be sent for booking a hall and all will be booked.
"http://127.0.0.1:8000/hall/confirm_book/1"
Response:"Booking confirmed for HallA from 2021-01-21T16:10:00+05:30 to 2021-01-21T17:10:00+05:30"

api for listing all halls: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/halls
api for listing all bookings: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/booking
api for creating a booking: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/createBooking

Note: I am busy with my office work so have not implemented login/logout so You can create a superuser using  "python manage.py createsuperuser" and check the functionalities.
Also.this applications in just to show the functionality in django So,didn't spend lot of time in designing the app.